title: Boyhood
creator: Leo Tolstoy
description: LibriVox recording of Boyhood by Leo Tolstoy. Read by Bill Boerst. Boyhood is the second in Tolstoy's trilogy of three autobiographical novels, including Childhood and Youth, published in a literary journal during the 1850s. (Introduction by Bill Boerst) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: audiobook; Tolstoy; Russian literature; Childhood; Youth; autobiography; autobiographical novel; librivox; trilogy
